    ],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-11-05-20-20-28.png"
  ),

  "figure-8.7": (
    caption: [
      Photo of Epsilon wasps demonstrating *female-defense polygyny* where males guard clustered emergent females and can mate with many virgins; use to exemplify ecological drivers (female clustering and synchronous emergence) that favor polygyny.
    ],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-11-05-20-21-01.png"
  ),

  "figure-8.8": (
    caption: [
